# Database (Prisma + PostgreSQL)

## Key Models
- `TelegramAccount` — self-referencing hierarchy via `parentId`, one `isHub`
- `ChatFork` — local chat fork; `telegramChatId` nullable for `OFFLINE_JOURNAL`
- `Message` — `localId` (UUID) for client-side identity; `telegramMessageId` nullable
- `MediaFile` — server-side `localPath`, optional `telegramFileId`

## Enums
- `ChatSyncMode`: chat-level sync behavior
- `MessageSyncStatus`: per-message sync state (distinct from ChatSyncMode)

## Unique Constraints
- `(accountId, telegramChatId)` — one fork per TG chat per account
- `(chatForkId, localId)` — client dedup
- `(chatForkId, telegramMessageId)` — TG dedup

## Migrations
```bash
cd backend && npx prisma migrate dev --name <name>
```

## Docker DB
PostgreSQL runs on port **5433** (5432 often occupied locally):
```bash
npm run db:up
```
